#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:5
msgid "**Akarsh Simha**"
msgstr "**Akarsh Simha**"

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:7
#| msgid ""
#| "The cosmic distance ladder refers to the succession of different methods "
#| "that astronomers use to measure distances to objects in the sky. Some "
#| "methods, like <link linkend=\"ai-parallax\">parallax</link>, work well "
#| "for only nearby objects. Other methods, like using the "
#| "<firstterm>cosmological redshift</firstterm>, work only for very distance "
#| "galaxies. Thus, there are several methods, each with its own limited "
#| "validity, and hence the name."
msgid ""
"The cosmic distance ladder refers to the succession of different methods "
"that astronomers use to measure distances to objects in the sky. Some "
"methods, like :doc:`parallax  <ai-parallax>`, work well for only nearby "
"objects. Other methods, like using the *cosmological redshift*, work only "
"for very distance galaxies. Thus, there are several methods, each with its "
"own limited validity, and hence the name."
msgstr ""
"L'escala de distàncies còsmiques es refereix a la successió dels mètodes "
"diferents que els astrònoms utilitzen per a mesurar distàncies a objectes en "
"el cel. Alguns mètodes, com la :doc:`paral·laxi <ai-parallax>`, només "
"funcionen bé amb els objectes propers. Altres mètodes, com utilitzar el "
"*desplaçament cap al roig*, només funcionen amb galàxies a molta distància. "
"Per tant, hi ha diversos mètodes, cadascun amb la seva pròpia validesa "
"limitada, d'aquí el seu nom."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:19
msgid "Direct measurements"
msgstr "Mesures directes"

# skip-rule: t-acc_obe
#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:21
#| msgid ""
#| "The bottom of the ladder consists of objects whose distances can be "
#| "directly measured, like the moon (see <ulink url=\"https://en.wikipedia."
#| "org/wiki/Lunar_Laser_Ranging_experiment\">Lunar Laser Ranging</ulink>). "
#| "The same technique, using radio waves, is applied to find distances to "
#| "planets as well."
msgid ""
"The bottom of the ladder consists of objects whose distances can be directly "
"measured, like the moon (see `Lunar Laser Ranging <https://en.wikipedia.org/"
"wiki/Lunar_Laser_Ranging_experiment>`__). The same technique, using radio "
"waves, is applied to find distances to planets as well."
msgstr ""
"La part inferior de l'escala es compon d'objectes amb distàncies que es "
"poden mesurar directament, com la Lluna (vegeu `Lunar Laser Ranging "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lunar_Laser_Ranging_experiment>`__). La "
"mateixa tècnica, utilitzant ones de ràdio, s'aplica també per a trobar les "
"distàncies als planetes."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:27
#| msgid ""
#| "For nearby stars, measuring the <link linkend=\"ai-parallax\">parallax</"
#| "link> is possible and yields the distance to the star."
msgid ""
"For nearby stars, measuring the :doc:`parallax  <ai-parallax>` is possible "
"and yields the distance to the star."
msgstr ""
"Per a les estrelles properes, és possible mesurar la :doc:`paral·laxi "
"<ai-parallax>` i s'obté la distància a l'estrella."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:34
msgid "Standard candles"
msgstr "Candeles estàndard"

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:36
#| msgid ""
#| "\"Standard candles\" are objects whose intrinsic brightnesses we can know "
#| "for sure. The apparent <link linkend=\"ai-magnitude\">magnitude</link>, "
#| "which is easy to measure, tells us how bright an object appears, not how "
#| "bright it actually is. Distant objects appear less brighter, because "
#| "their light gets spread out over a larger area."
msgid ""
"\"Standard candles\" are objects whose intrinsic brightnesses we can know "
"for sure. The apparent :doc:`magnitude  <ai-magnitude>`, which is easy to "
"measure, tells us how bright an object appears, not how bright it actually "
"is. Distant objects appear less brighter, because their light gets spread "
"out over a larger area."
msgstr ""
"Les «candeles estàndard» són objectes amb una lluminositat intrínseca que "
"podem saber del cert. La :doc:`magnitud <ai-magnitude>` aparent, la qual és "
"fàcil de mesurar, ens explica com sembla de lluminós un objecte, no com de "
"lluminós és en realitat. Els objectes distants semblen menys lluminosos, pel "
"fet que la seva llum s'estén sobre una àrea més gran."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:43
#| msgid ""
#| "In accordance with the <firstterm>inverse square law</firstterm> for "
#| "light intensities, the amount of light we receive from an object drops "
#| "with the distance squared. Thus, we may compute the distance to an object "
#| "if we know both how bright it actually is (absolute magnitude; 'M') and "
#| "how bright it appears to us on earth (apparent magnitude; 'm'). We may "
#| "define the <firstterm>distance modulus</firstterm> as follows:"
msgid ""
"In accordance with the *inverse square law* for light intensities, the "
"amount of light we receive from an object drops with the distance squared. "
"Thus, we may compute the distance to an object if we know both how bright it "
"actually is (absolute magnitude; 'M') and how bright it appears to us on "
"earth (apparent magnitude; 'm'). We may define the *distance modulus* as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""
"D'acord amb la *llei del quadrat invers* de la intensitat de la llum, la "
"quantitat de llum que rebem d'un objecte decau amb el quadrat de la "
"distància. Per tant, podem calcular la distància a un objecte si sabem tant "
"la lluminositat que té en realitat (magnitud absoluta, «M») i com de "
"lluminosa ens sembla a la Terra (magnitud aparent; «m»). Podem definir el "
"*mòdul de la distància* de la manera següent:"

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:51
#| msgid "Distance Modulus = M - m = 5 log<subscript>10</subscript> d - 5"
msgid "Distance Modulus = M - m = 5 log\\ :sub:`10` d - 5"
msgstr "Mòdul de la distància = M - m = 5 log\\ :sub:`10` d - 5"

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:53
#| msgid ""
#| "Here 'd' is the distance measured in <link linkend=\"ai-parallax"
#| "\">parsecs</link>."
msgid "Here 'd' is the distance measured in :doc:`parsecs  <ai-parallax>`."
msgstr "Aquí, «d» és la distància mesurada en :doc:`parsecs <ai-parallax>`."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:56
msgid ""
"For these special standard candle objects, we have some other way of knowing "
"their intrinsic brightness, and thereby can calculate their distance."
msgstr ""
"Per a aquests objectes de candela estàndard especials, tenim una altra manera "
"de conèixer la seva lluminositat intrínseca i, per tant, podrem calcular la "
"seva distància."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:60
msgid "Common \"standard candles\" used in astronomy are:"
msgstr "Les «candeles estàndard» d'ús general en l'astronomia són:"

# Nota: https://ca.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cefeida
# skip-rule: punctuation-period-no
#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:61
msgid ""
"Cepheid Variables: A kind of periodic variable star, whose variation period "
"is related to the luminosity"
msgstr ""
"Cefeides variables: És una classe particular d'estrella de període variable, "
"la lluminositat de la qual varia de forma periòdica."

# skip-rule: punctuation-period-no, barb-uns
#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:64
msgid ""
"RR Lyrae Variables: Another such periodic variable star with a well-known "
"period-luminosity relationship"
msgstr ""
"RR Lyrae variables: Unes altres estrelles de període variable amb una "
"relació de període-lluminositat conegut."

# skip-rule: punctuation-period-no
#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:67
msgid ""
"Type-Ia supernovae: These supernovae have a very well-defined luminosity as "
"a result of the physics that governs them and hence serve as standard-candles"
msgstr ""
"Supernoves de tipus Ia: Aquestes supernoves tenen una lluminositat molt ben "
"definida, com a resultat de la física que les governa i, per tant, serveixen "
"com a candeles estàndard."

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:74
msgid "Other methods"
msgstr "Altres mètodes"

#: ../../user_manual/ai-cosmicdist.rst:76
#| msgid ""
#| "There are many other methods. Some of them rely on the physics of stars, "
#| "such as the relationship between luminosity and color for various types "
#| "of stars (this is usually represented on a <firstterm>Hertzsprung-Russel "
#| "Diagram</firstterm>). Some of them work for star clusters, such as the "
#| "<firstterm>Moving cluster method</firstterm> and the <firstterm>main-"
#| "sequence fitting method</firstterm>. The <firstterm>Tully-Fisher "
#| "relation</firstterm> that relates the brightness of a spiral galaxy to "
#| "its rotation can be used to find the distance modulus, since the rotation "
#| "of a galaxy is easy to measure using <firstterm>Doppler shift</"
#| "firstterm>. Distances to distant galaxies may be found by measuring the "
#| "<firstterm>Cosmological redshift</firstterm>, which is the redshift of "
#| "light from distance galaxies that results from the expansion of the "
#| "universe."
msgid ""
"There are many other methods. Some of them rely on the physics of stars, "
"such as the relationship between luminosity and color for various types of "
"stars (this is usually represented on a *Hertzsprung-Russel Diagram*). Some "
"of them work for star clusters, such as the *Moving cluster method* and the "
"*main-sequence fitting method*. The *Tully-Fisher relation* that relates the "
"brightness of a spiral galaxy to its rotation can be used to find the "
"distance modulus, since the rotation of a galaxy is easy to measure using "
"*Doppler shift*. Distances to distant galaxies may be found by measuring the "
"*Cosmological redshift*, which is the redshift of light from distance "
"galaxies that results from the expansion of the universe."
msgstr ""
"Hi ha molts altres mètodes. Alguns es basen en la física de les estrelles, "
"com la relació entre la lluminositat i el color per a tipus diferents "
"d'estrelles (això se sol representar en un *diagrama de Hertzsprung-"
"Russell*). Alguns funcionen per als cúmuls d'estrelles, com ara el *mètode "
"de moviment del cúmul* i el *mètode d'ajust de la seqüència principal*. La "
"*relació de Tully-Fisher* que relaciona la lluminositat d'una galàxia "
"espiral amb la seva rotació es pot utilitzar per a trobar el mòdul de la "
"distància, ja que la rotació d'una galàxia és fàcil de mesurar utilitzant "
"l'*efecte Doppler*. Es poden trobar les distàncies a les galàxies distants "
"mesurant el *desplaçament cap al roig*, el qual és el desplaçament cap al "
"roig de la llum de galàxies distants resultant de l'expansió de l'univers."

